executor_display_name: Initiate a raw data download request.
executor_description: This request can be used to download device sensor data for specified users for a given time range of an organization. This is an asynchronous call that triggers a data download job request. The success or failure of the job request will be delivered to the specified target email as part of the request api If successful, the email will contain a downloadable url link to a zipped file containing the sensor data. The downloadable url link is only valid for 5 hours after that the link becomes invalid. You can only send download request simultaneously for 10 users max and a 1 week time range

queryParams.description: TargetEmail is the email address to which the success/failure of the download job request is sent along with the actual url link to download the data from.
Example: start_time=2022-07-15T02:34:51-06:30 StartTimeRFC3339 is the time range to download the data for, in RFC339 format.
Example: end_time=2022-07-15T18:34:51-06:30 EndTimeRFC3339 is the end of the time range to download the data for, in RFC339 format.
Example: user_ids=abcdefgh123456789,pqrstubwx987654321 UserIDs is the list of user ID strings to download the data for.

Example: data_to_download=accel,ppg DataToDownload is a list of string enums indicating the type of data to download.  Possible values are ["accel", "gyro", "ppg"] for accelerometer, gyroscope, and ppg waveform data, respectively.

Example: output_file_formats=csv,parquet OutputFileFormats is a list of string enums indicating the file formats in which the data download file will be sent as.  Possible values are ["csv", "parqut"] NOTE: parquet files could be 2 to -10 times smaller than csv files.

AnonymizeIDs is a boolean flag which determines what user label is used Where True means biostrap pseudo-random internal user identifier False means Biostrap email ID (does not need to be an email, can be assigned a custom string ID on account creation) NOTE: Default is False

executor_display_name: Lock or Unlock Device to an Organization User
executor_description: If device is already locked to another user, it will return a status=failed and status_message = "device is locked to another user" in the response. If device is successfully locked or unlocked from a user, it will return status=success in the response.

queryParams.description: UserID of the Organization User

Enum: "dt_biostrap_wristband" "dt_biostrap_shoepod" Example: device_type=dt_biostrap_wristband DeviceType is the type of the device.  Possible device type strings are ["dt_biostrap_wristband", "dt_biostrap_shoepod"]

Example: device_mac_address_or_id_encoded=62134192413234 DeviceMacAddressOrIDEncoded is the encoded Mac Address of the device or the encoded Device ID of the user.  In most general cases, it will be an encoded Mac Address that you receive either by calling a different API or by scanning the biostrap devices which will have physical barcaode labeled on the device.

Enum: "lock" "unlock" Example: operation=lock Operation is the operation of the association requested.  Possible values are ["lock", "unlock"] if operation=lock, lock the provided device_type, device_mac_address_or_id to the user_id if operation=unlock, unlock the provided device_type, device_mac_address_or_id from the user_id

executor_display_name: Get User Calorie Details With Granularity
executor_description: Returns user calorie detail with daily, weekly, monthly or yearly granularity based on query parameter field. No pagination is involved.

queryParams.description: This parameter is required for Organization (API Key) requests, the user_id is implicit in OAuth2 user requests

integer <int32> Example: user_timezone_offset_in_mins=-420 UserTimezoneOffsetInMins is used to find the user's resting calories for the current day if this falls in the requested date range. If this value is sent as 0 or not sent, in that case the resting calories for the current day will get calculated based on the GMT timezone.  NOTE: this field is only required when the provided date is equal to the current dayy and if it is not sent, the only issue will be with the resting calories calcuation of the current day.  For eg: -420 for -07:00, i.e 7 hour west of GMT, in other words, Pacific Time

string Example: date=2021-07-12 Date in YYYYY-MM-DD format (eg: 2021-07-12 for July 12, 2021) for the calorie details,  if granularity=day, it return calories for the given date.  if graunalarity>day, it returns calorie details in a date range with the end date being this given date.

string Enum: "day" "week" "month" "year" Example: granularity=week Granularity of Calorie details, possible values = [day, week, month, year]  if granularity=day, it returns calorie details for the given date.  if granularity=week or granularity=month, it returns calorie details in a date range with end date = given date and start date = <6, 29> days in the past from the end date (i.e the given date) which is a total of <7, 30> days of data for granularity = <week, month> respectively.  if granularity=year, it returns monthly calorie details for the last 12 months.
